# Title: Use Next.js App Router + shadcn/ui + Tailwind (no ad-hoc CSS)
# Scope: project
You MUST:
- Use Next.js App Router (src/app) and server components by default where appropriate.
- Use shadcn/ui for primitives and patterns. Do NOT author raw CSS files or CSS Modules unless explicitly asked; style via Tailwind utility classes.
- Generate new UI with `pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add <component>` and place components in src/components/ui following shadcn conventions.
- Use Tailwind for layout/spacing/typography. Avoid inline styles except for dynamic values.

Docs to follow:
- shadcn for Next.js: https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/installation/next
- Tailwind + Next.js: https://tailwindcss.com/docs/guides/nextjs
